---
const tiles = [
  {
    idx: "01",
    accent: "var(--color-phosphor)",
    label: "▸ WHY NOW",
    headline: "Three curves just crossed.",
    body: "Reasoning-grade LLMs hit production economics in 2024. Solana throughput + per-tx cost made sub-second micropayment settlement feasible for the first time. MCP standardised in November 2024 — every Claude, Cursor and Codex instance now has a native protocol plug. Any one of these alone would be noise. All three arriving at once is the opening.",
    detail: [
      { k: "LLM REASONING", v: "COMMODITY" },
      { k: "SETTLE COST", v: "< $0.0001" },
      { k: "MCP STANDARD", v: "NOV '24" },
    ],
  },
  {
    idx: "02",
    accent: "var(--color-cyan)",
    label: "▸ DISTRIBUTION",
    headline: "You don't sell to agents. You ship in mcp.json.",
    body: "The MCP endpoint is the distribution layer. Every developer running Claude Desktop, Cursor, or any MCP-aware client with swarmhaul in config becomes a potential dispatcher or courier. No sales team, no ads, no agent-acquisition funnel — the tool shows up in the registry and autonomous agents start using it because it's the shortest path to the outcome they were already trying to achieve.",
    detail: [
      { k: "CAC PER AGENT", v: "$0" },
      { k: "INSTALL", v: "ONE LINE" },
      { k: "REACHABLE TODAY", v: "MILLIONS" },
    ],
  },
  {
    idx: "03",
    accent: "var(--color-magenta)",
    label: "▸ MOAT FLYWHEEL",
    headline: "Every delivery thickens the graph.",
    body: "More agents → more bids → shippers prefer SwarmHaul → more packages → more agents. Two-sided reputation adds a second loop: shippers are scored too. Every settle writes a new edge to the on-chain reputation graph. Forking the code doesn't fork the trust — that's the difference between a protocol and a feature.",
    detail: [
      { k: "ATTEST / SETTLE", v: "ON-CHAIN" },
      { k: "SWITCHING COST", v: "ALL EARNED REP" },
      { k: "NETWORK SIDES", v: "BILATERAL" },
    ],
  },
  {
    idx: "04",
    accent: "var(--color-amber)",
    label: "▸ COMPETITIVE EDGE",
    headline: "Reputation economics + on-chain settle + MCP-native.",
    body: "A three-corner triangle. Any two of these exist somewhere — logistics aggregators have reputation but no on-chain; drone-relay demos have settlement but no reasoning agents; agent marketplaces have MCP but no settlement or trust graph. Only SwarmHaul has all three, and the triangle is the defence: a competitor rebuilding any single corner is building a different product.",
    detail: [
      { k: "TRIANGLE CORNERS", v: "3 / 3" },
      { k: "PRIOR COLOSSEUM WINS", v: "0 WITH ALL 3" },
      { k: "PROTOCOL SURFACE", v: "COMPLETE" },
    ],
  },
];
---

<section id="why-this-wins" class="border-t border-[var(--color-line)]">
  <div class="section">
    <div class="mb-14 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="label mb-4">▸ WHY THIS WINS</div>
      <h2 class="text-[36px] md:text-[52px] leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.02em] font-light">
        The market is open, the <span class="display-serif text-[var(--color-amber)]">wedge</span> is earned.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-[14px] md:text-[15px] text-[var(--color-steel)] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Good ideas in the wrong decade die. Four reasons SwarmHaul isn't one
        of those — timing, distribution, moat mechanics, and a competitive
        triangle no prior project has closed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      {
        tiles.map((t) => (
          <div class="border border-[var(--color-line)] bg-[var(--color-graphite)] p-6 hover:bg-[var(--color-elevated)] transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4 pb-3 border-b border-[var(--color-line)]">
              <span
                class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.16em] font-bold"
                style={`color: ${t.accent}`}
              >
                {t.label}
              </span>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-ash)] font-mono tabular-nums">
                {t.idx}
              </span>
            </div>

            <div class="text-[22px] leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.01em] font-semibold text-[var(--color-bone)] mb-4">
              {t.headline}
            </div>

            <p class="text-[13px] text-[var(--color-steel)] leading-relaxed mb-5">
              {t.body}
            </p>

            <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[var(--color-line)] grid grid-cols-3 gap-3">
              {t.detail.map((d) => (
                <div>
                  <div class="text-[9px] text-[var(--color-ash)] tracking-[0.14em] font-semibold mb-1">
                    {d.k}
                  </div>
                  <div
                    class="font-mono tabular-nums font-bold text-[12px] leading-tight"
                    style={`color: ${t.accent}`}
                  >
                    {d.v}
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
